DT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the premium/discount between perpetual and index prices. The funding rate is determined by the Interest Rate (0.01%) and Premium Index, with a maximum rate of ±0.75% per funding interval. Positions held at funding time automatically pay or receive funding based on their direction and the current rate."}]]}],"$L3",["$L4","$L5","$L6"],"$L7"]}],"$L8"]}]]}],["$L9","$La"],"$Lb"]}],"loading":null,"isPartial":false}
3:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","W","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"W token's relatively smaller market cap compared to major cryptocurrencies can create more volatile funding rate swings, presenting arbitrage opportunities. The infrastructure-focused nature of Wormhole creates distinct trading patterns as the token responds to cross-chain activity and protocol developments, often diverging from broader market sentiment."}]]}]
4:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"W/USDT funding rates on Bybit have shown periods of sustained positive rates during network growth phases, reaching 0.2-0.4% per 8-hour interval. The pair experiences notable funding spikes during major bridge updates or cross-chain integration announcements. Lower liquidity compared to major pairs means funding rates can persist at elevated levels for extended periods, creating longer-term arbitrage windows. Weekend periods often see reduced activity leading to more neutral funding rates."}]]}]
5:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategy"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange funding arbitrage works best when W/USDT shows significant rate differentials between Bybit and other platforms. Bybit's unified margin system allows efficient capital allocation across multiple positions for delta-neutral strategies. The 8-hour funding interval provides sufficient time to execute hedge positions on spot markets or other derivatives platforms. Monitor correlation with SOL and other cross-chain tokens that often move in similar funding cycles."}]]}]
6:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"W token's infrastructure focus creates exposure to smart contract risks and cross-chain bridge vulnerabilities that can cause sudden price gaps. Lower trading volume means larger position sizes can impact funding calculations and create slippage during position adjustments. Bybit's auto-deleveraging system activates more frequently on smaller pairs during volatile periods. Consider position sizing relative to open interest and maintain adequate margin buffers for unexpected volatility spikes in the Wormhole ecosystem."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"What makes W/USDT funding rates on Bybit unique?","answer":"W/USDT on Bybit benefits from the exchange's strong derivatives infrastructure while offering exposure to cross-chain bridge activity. The smaller market cap creates more volatile funding rate cycles compared to major tokens, with rates often reflecting specific Wormhole ecosystem developments rather than just general market sentiment."},{"question":"How often are W/USDT funding rates calculated on Bybit?","answer":"Bybit calculates W/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The rate is based on the 8-hour time-weighted average premium between the perpetual price and the underlying index price, with a maximum rate cap of ±0.75% per interval."},{"question":"What are the optimal position sizes for W/USDT arbitrage?","answer":"Due to W's smaller market cap, positions above $50,000-100,000 may start impacting local liquidity on Bybit. Monitor the order book depth and consider the 24-hour volume when sizing arbitrage positions. Bybit's unified margin allows for efficient capital usage, but maintain 30-50% buffer margins due to W's volatility."},{"question":"Can I use Bybit's unified margin for W/USDT arbitrage strategies?","answer":"Yes, Bybit's unified margin account allows you to use the same collateral for W/USDT perpetuals and other instruments simultaneously. This enables efficient delta-neutral strategies where you can hedge W exposure with correlated assets like SOL or maintain portfolio-wide risk management across multiple arbitrage positions."}]}]
